content: Hi all. During triage this week, I am seeing a couple cases where a bunch of doc benchmarks have regressed. A representative from T-rustdoc team has hypothesized that it is spurious, because the rollup in question contains only seemingly innocuous rustdoc changes. My question: Is there a way to see graphs for the performance over time for the doc generation benchmarks?
You can manually click "next" on the compare page though.
do we have any kind of graphs for the -doc benchmarks btw?
I havn't seen them on the https://perf.rust-lang.org/ landing page yet I think
I went to move this message to a new thread, and it turns out the question was asked recently ;)
No, I never implemented them when I added support for rustdoc
It shouldn't be too hard, all the data is there, you just need to find how it's done for the rustc benchmarks and copy it
